<Stem>
	<Paragraph><Sentence>Give the first 3 terms of an arithmetic sequence that satisfies the following:</Sentence> 
        </Paragraph>
        <Blockquote>
	  <Paragraph><Sentence>1. The first term is a positive integer between 24 and 26, inclusive.</Sentence> 
          </Paragraph>
	  <Paragraph><Sentence>2. The common difference is a negative integer between -5 and -3, inclusive.</Sentence> 
          </Paragraph>
        </Blockquote>
        <Paragraph><Sentence>
          <Emphasis>Note:</Emphasis> There is more than one correct answer. Any example 
           you choose that meets the above requirements will be scored as correct.   
